    "narrative": "LawDog\u2019s lineup today is anchored by **Cal Raleigh** (70.13) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (69.12), our two strongest plays. **Cal Raleigh** benefits from a soft matchup against Matthew Liberatore, and while his lineup position is technically pending, the projected #2 slot provides a significant boost to his counting stats. **Geraldo Perdomo** is our primary source of speed today, and despite a 36% rain risk, his leadoff spot against the hittable Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez makes him essential for our stolen base targets. **Will Smith** (68.07) also commands a \"Strong\" start designation, bolstered by a favorable wind forecast and an advantageous matchup against Colin Rea.\n\nStrategic benching was critical today, with **Yainer Diaz** (51.72) missing the cut by the narrowest of margins. While **Yainer Diaz** offers solid efficiency against Ryan Weathers, the optimizer preferred the superior lineup protection and superior dynamic platoon edges afforded to our lower-tier starters like **Jung Hoo Lee** and **Gavin Sheets**. We are keeping a close eye on **Geraldo Perdomo** and **Gavin Sheets**, as their games carry a 36% rain risk; should those contests be scrubbed, we will pivot to **Gleyber Torres**, who was the next man up on our bench at 50.37.\n\nFinally, we are monitoring **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (59.85) carefully. His score is suppressed slightly by a poor historical BvP against Kevin Gausman, but his raw talent and #3 order placement necessitate a start. Conversely, while **Daulton Varsho** and **Jeremiah Jackson** sit at the bottom of our active lineup (45.71), they maintain their spots because of our need to avoid unnecessary game cap depletion while keeping high-upside options available against challenging arms like Crochet. We remain aggressive in the SB category, leaning on the slow delivery times against Eury P\u00e9rez to help **Matt Chapman**, **Luis Arraez**, and **Jung Hoo Lee** stay relevant.",
